## JAVA SDK

### Minimum requirements
- Java 1.7+

### Install the SDK
#### pom.xml
```xml
	<repositories>
		<repository>
			<id>Eclipse Paho Repo</id>
			<url>https://repo.eclipse.org/content/repositories/paho-snapshots/</url>
		</repository>
		<repository>
			<id>trackrr.io-release</id>
			<url>https://repo.trackrr.io/release</url>
			<releases>
				<enabled>true</enabled>
			</releases>
			<snapshots>
				<enabled>false</enabled>
			</snapshots>
		</repository>
		<repository>
			<id>trackrr.io-snapshot</id>
			<url>https://repo.trackrr.io/snapshot</url>
			<releases>
				<enabled>false</enabled>
			</releases>
			<snapshots>
				<enabled>true</enabled>
			</snapshots>
		</repository>
	</repositories>
```
```xml
<dependencies>
  <dependency>
    <groupId>jp.co.stylez.gps</groupId>
    <artifactId>gpsplotter-sdk-java</artifactId>
    <version>0.0.1-SNAPSHOT</version>
  </dependency>
</dependencies>
```
#### java code
```java
		final String gpsKey = "XXXXXXXXXXXXXXX";
		final String secret = "YYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYY";
		final GpsClientManager client = new GpsClientManager(gpsKey, secret);
		client.connect(new AWSIotMqttClientStatusCallback() {
			@Override
			public void onStatusChanged(final AWSIotMqttClientStatus status, final Throwable throwable) {
				if (status == AWSIotMqttClientStatus.Connected) {
					final Gps gps = new Gps();
					final Map<String, String> userData = new HashMap<>();
					gps.setGpsKey(gpsKey);
					gps.setCreatedDate(System.currentTimeMillis());
					gps.setUserData(userData);
					final Coords coords = new Coords();
					coords.setLatitude(33.79519271850586d);
					coords.setLongitude(-118.01104736328125d);
					gps.setCoords(coords);
					client.publish(gps);
				}
			}
		});
```
